  • Classes in absyn used by absyn 
    Class and Description
    Absyn
    A node of abstract syntax.
    ArithmeticBinOp
    A node of abstract syntax representing an arithmetic binary operation between two expressions, that is, a binary operation, such as addition or subtraction, that returns an int or float value.
    BinOp
    A node of abstract syntax representing a binary operation between two expressions.
    BooleanBinOp
    A node of abstract syntax representing a Boolean binary operation between two expressions, that is, a binary operation, such logical and or logical or, that operates on Booleans and returns a Boolean.
    ClassMemberDeclaration
    A node of abstract syntax representing the declaration of a class member i.e., a field, constructor or method of a Kitten class.
    CodeDeclaration
    A node of abstract syntax representing the declaration of a constructor or method of a Kitten class.
    Command
    A node of abstract syntax representing a Kitten command.
    ComparisonBinOp
    A node of abstract syntax representing a comparison binary operation between two expressions, that is, a binary operation, such as =, < or ≤, that compares two values and returns a Boolean value.
    Expression
    A node of abstract syntax representing a Kitten expression.
    ExpressionSeq
    A node of abstract syntax representing a sequence (list) of Kitten expressions.
    FormalParameters
    A node of abstract syntax representing the formal parameters of a Kitten method.
    Literal
    A node of abstract syntax representing a literal, that is, a syntactical representation of a run-time value.
    Lvalue
    A node of abstract syntax representing a leftvalue, that is, an expression which refers to the container of a value, and which can hence be used on the left of an assignment.
    NumericalComparisonBinOp
    A node of abstract syntax representing a comparison binary operation between two expressions, that is, a binary operation, such as < or ≤, that compares two numerical values and returns a Boolean value.
    TypeExpression
    A node of abstract syntax representing a Kitten type.
